Introduction

Seonyou is a South Korean singer, dancer and rapper under M25.

On September 21, 2020, Seonyou was announced as an upcoming contestant on the teen reality competition show "CAP-TEEN". She was eliminated after being unable to pass the first performance evaluation.

On September 8, 2021, Seonyou was revealed as a contestant on the MBC's survival show "My Teenage Girl". During the finale, she ranked second place with 241,178.9 votes, thus becoming a member of the girl group CLASS:y. CLASS:y made their debut on May 5, 2022 with the mini album "Class Is Over".

In 2022, she participated in the JTBC's survival show "The Second World", which allowed rappers to showcase their vocals through a singing competition.
